news.title: Godrej Properties buys TDR certificates for Gurugram project
news.para: This will help Godrej Properties construct an additional 300,000 sq ft of area, with a total revenue potential of Rs 900 crore, said people with knowledge of the matter.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires seven acres land in Bengaluru
news.para: residential project, having a developable potential of approximately nine lakh sq ft with an estimated revenue potential of about Rs 1,200 crore.

news.title: BAF and RERI sign MoU to spread awareness amongst homebuyers in Bengaluru
news.para: This partnership aims to benefit nearly 1,300 apartment and villa resident welfare associations (RWAs), representing almost 300,000 households and approximately one and a half million citizens.

news.title: Delhi metro looks to open three phase-IV corridors by 2026
news.para: Delhi Metro Rail Corporation (DMRC) officials said the Phase 4 expansion project is progressing rapidly with a target of opening all three priority corridors comprising 65 kilometres of new lines by 2026.

news.title: EOW registers FIR against Noida-based Prateek Group
news.para: The FIR – which followed a complaint by the 20 buyers of Prateek Edifice in Sector 107 – named the owners Prashant and Prateek Tiwari, and senior managers Sunil Kumar Mittal and Anshuman Sharma.

news.title: Kenya faces affordable housing shortage amidst growing urban population
news.para: The government plans to build 250,000 houses each year, aimed at eventually closing a housing deficit that World Bank data puts at 2 million units. The plan was launched in 2022, but no data is available on the number of houses already completed.

news.title: Telangana CM asks officials to prepare Warrangal's master plan 2050
news.para: The chief minister suggested to them developing the proposed Outer Ring Road in such a way to connect one national highway with another in the city.

news.title: Housing ministry extends smart cities mission deadline till March 2025
news.para: "In the larger interests of the public, CM Revanth Reddy pleaded with the Central government for the extension of the Smart City Mission until the works are completed.

news.title: Registration of properties in Mumbai rise by 12% in June 2024: Report
news.para: The figure is expected to reach around 11,600 units this month, the bulk of the registration is of housing properties, Strong buyer confidence in Mumbai has kept property sales above the 10,000 mark in each of the six months of 2024 calendar year.

news.title: Rajasthan government forms new committee to probe single lease cases
news.para: It is noteworthy that during the tenure of the previous government, a committee was constituted to withdraw the case from the court on the irregularities in the single lease case.

news.title: Sweden's SBB creditors exchange debt for residential bonds in $158 million swap
news.para: SBB is at the centre of a Swedish property market bubble that began to unravel in 2022 when inflation and interest rates soared, triggering sharp cuts to its credit ratings and a plunge in its share price.

news.title: Government to reconstruct 28,643 dilapidated flats: Tamil Nadu CM
news.para: The Board currently maintains 1.94 lakh flats across Tamil Nadu and among them, 28,643 dwellings have been found to be dilapidated, the chief minister said.

news.title: New home sales in NCR increase by 6% in Q2 2024: Anarock
news.para: Not just this, NCR also saw a whopping 134% increase in new launches against Q1 2024, with approximately 17,030 units launched in Q2 2024.

news.title: State government asks Centre to grant approval for Bengaluru metro third phase
news.para: The State Government of Karnataka is actively pursuing approvals for two critical phases of the Bangalore Metro Rail project, urging the Central Government to expedite the process.

news.title: Mumbai: MMRDA to raise Rs 850-crore from KfW to develop urban infrastructure
news.para: The funds procured from KfW and MMRDA's resources will be primarily allocated towards various sustainable development projects within and around the Mumbai Metropolitan Region

news.title: Lucknow development body to commence land acquisition for four housing schemes
news.para: LDA chairperson and divisional commissioner Roshan Jacob approved the proposal for land acquisition for the projects during a meeting on Friday.

news.title: Karnataka government urges Centre to create GIFT City, fast-track approvals
news.para: In a statement by the minister's office, Kharge said that Karnataka wants to set up a Central Business District that will act as a global financial and IT hub.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires leasehold rights for 11 acre land in Pune
news.para: The project has a developable potential of approximately 2.2 million sq ft with an estimated revenue potential of about Rs 1,800 crore.

news.title: Implement M-sand policy at the earliest: Uttar Pradesh CM
news.para: The CM has also asked the department to simplify the process of issuing licences. The process should be streamlined at the district level with a defined timeline.

news.title: Amitabh Bachchan buys two apartments in Mumbai’s Borivali suburb
news.para: The deal comes immediately after the veteran actor recently purchased three more office properties spread across three floors in a commercial project in Oshiwara locality of Mumbai’s western suburb of Andheri.
